response.overview: Reality-TV - Relive the most memorable moments of the hit reality show that searched for a lead singer to replace late INXS front man Michael Hutchence -- and came up with a worthy winner in singer J.D. Fortune. Tracks include Fortune's "California Dreamin'," Suzie McNeil's "Bohemian Rhapsody," Miguel Ayesa's "Kiss from a Rose" and Marty Casey's "Baby One More Time," plus the new INXS performing "Need You Tonight," "Never Tear Us Apart" and "Suicide Blonde." -  MiG Ayesa, Brandon Calhoon, Neal Carlson
response.title: Rock Star: INXS - The DVD
